ğŸ‘‰ So: make = the engine of the native build.

â˜• maven in MAINLINE
Where used:
Not in the core build stage.
It comes in when the job interacts with Ciscoâ€™s internal Maven repo (https://engci-maven-master.cisco.com).
That repo is referenced for Java dependencies and artifacts â€” for example, build-support or notification components (like cms-build-notify-2024).

What it does:
Handles downloading/publishing Java-based tools the pipeline needs.
Example: notification modules, packaging helpers, or supporting libraries.

Output:
JARs/WARs used by the build scripts (not the OVA directly).
ğŸ‘‰ So: maven = used indirectly, for Java components & dependency fetching.

âœ… Combined picture for MAINLINE
make â†’ runs inside the build containers, compiles everything, produces Linux images and VM outputs.
maven â†’ supports the job by fetching/using Java tools and dependencies (from Ciscoâ€™s internal Maven repo).

